body:
@johnyNJ @WeichenXu123 Thank you for raising this issue and discussing solutions. Here's my proposal:

1. Increase the minimum parameter value length supported by all backends to 500, as documented in https://mlflow.org/docs/latest/rest-api.html#log-param. This will require a database migration for `SqlAlchemyStore`, which current defines `value` as a length-500 column: https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/2037b384f3cef6c2e8828ec68201040bc3790235/mlflow/store/tracking/dbmodels/models.py#L410. It also requires adjusting length-checking logic in backend validation utilities (https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/8693a26bf2acd418aa93aa5ea2e5536caa199fc3/mlflow/utils/validation.py#L148), as pointed out by @WeichenXu123.

2. Fix the documentation for `mlflow.log_param()` to reflect that all backend stores support values up to length *500*, instead of *5000*. Also update the REST API documentation (https://mlflow.org/docs/latest/rest-api.html#log-param) to indicate that some backends may support larger parameter values (e.g. third-party backends).

3. Remove all *client-side* validation of parameter length from `log_param()` / `log_params()`, if any is present. Backends should perform all necessary validations.

4. Adjust autologging behavior to only truncate parameters to length-500, rather than length-250.

@johnyNJ @WeichenXu123 Let me know what you think of this proposal. We are open to supporting longer values, though we'd like to understand the use case(s) first.
